### C2 — Webhook uses global HMAC secret, not per-tenant

**Files:** `server/src/routes/webhooks.routes.ts`, `server/src/utils/hmac.ts`

Migration `00034` correctly adds `paymob_hmac_secret_enc` per tenant, but the webhook handler uses a global `process.env.PAYMOB_HMAC_SECRET`. With multiple tenants each having their own Paymob merchant account, this will reject valid webhooks or accept forged ones.

```ts
// ❌ CURRENT
const secret = process.env.PAYMOB_HMAC_SECRET ?? "";
if (!verifyPaymobHmac(payload, hmac, secret)) { ... }

// ✅ FIX — look up tenant from reservation/payment first, then verify with their secret
const orderId = String(payload.merchant_order_id ?? "");

const { data: reservation } = await supabaseAdmin
  .from("reservations").select("id, status, tenant_id").eq("id", orderId).maybeSingle();
const { data: payment } = !reservation
  ? await supabaseAdmin.from("payments").select("id, status, tenant_id").eq("id", orderId).maybeSingle()
  : { data: null };

const tenantId = reservation?.tenant_id ?? payment?.tenant_id;
if (!tenantId) return res.json({ received: true });

const { data: tenant } = await supabaseAdmin
  .from("tenants").select("paymob_hmac_secret_enc").eq("id", tenantId).single();

const secret = tenant?.paymob_hmac_secret_enc
  ? decrypt(tenant.paymob_hmac_secret_enc, process.env.ENCRYPTION_KEY!)
  : (process.env.PAYMOB_HMAC_SECRET ?? "");

if (!verifyPaymobHmac(payload, hmac, secret)) { ... }
```

**Impact:** Webhooks either never verify (all pass) or always fail (all payments stuck at `pending`).

