### C6 — `"rejected"` status doesn't exist in DB `reservation_status` enum

**Files:** `client/src/features/reservation/types.ts`, `server/src/routes/agent.routes.ts`

The FE type has `status: "pending" | "confirmed" | "cancelled" | "rejected"` and the agent route schema allows patching to `"rejected"` — but the DB enum only has `('pending', 'confirmed', 'cancelled', 'expired')`.

```ts
// ❌ client/src/features/reservation/types.ts
status: "pending" | "confirmed" | "cancelled" | "rejected";

// ✅ Fix
status: "pending" | "confirmed" | "cancelled" | "expired";
```

```ts
// ❌ server/src/routes/agent.routes.ts
const statusSchema = z.object({ status: z.enum(["confirmed", "cancelled", "rejected"]) });

// ✅ Fix — also add role-based constraint
