### C7 — CORS single-origin breaks multi-tenant custom domains

**Files:** `server/src/index.ts`

```ts
// ❌ CURRENT
app.use(cors({ origin: process.env.CLIENT_URL ?? "http://localhost:3000" }));

// ✅ FIX — dynamic CORS
const allowedOrigins = (process.env.ALLOWED_ORIGINS ?? "http://localhost:3000").split(",");

app.use(cors({
  origin: (origin, callback) => {
    if (!origin) return callback(null, true); // non-browser clients
    const allowed =
      allowedOrigins.some(o => origin === o.trim()) ||
      origin.endsWith(`.${process.env.ROOT_DOMAIN ?? "yourdomain.com"}`);
    callback(allowed ? null : new Error("Not allowed by CORS"), allowed);
  },
  credentials: true,
}));
```

**Impact:** All tenants with custom domains get CORS errors on every API call.

