## 🔐 SECURITY

---

### S1 — No encryption key rotation strategy for `paymob_api_key_enc`

The `decrypt()` function uses a static `ENCRYPTION_KEY`. If the key is leaked, all stored API keys are unrecoverable. Add key versioning:

```ts
// ✅ Encode version in encrypted value:
// v1:{iv_hex}:{ciphertext_hex}
// When decrypting: parse version, use the key for that version
// When rotating: re-encrypt all existing values with new key in a migration script
```

---

### S2 — No rate limiting on reservation or waitlist creation

Malicious actors can lock units or flood the waitlist:

```ts
const reservationLimiter = rateLimit({ windowMs: 60_000, max: 5 });
const waitlistLimiter    = rateLimit({ windowMs: 60_000, max: 10 });
app.use("/api/v1/reservations", reservationLimiter);
app.use("/api/v1/waiting-list", waitlistLimiter);
```

---

### S3 — No JSONB structure validation for `theme_config` and `filter_schema`

Arbitrary JSONB accepted from clients could inject unexpected keys. Validate structure server-side on tenant update:

```ts
const themeConfigSchema = z.object({
  primary_color: z.string().regex(/^#[0-9a-fA-F]{6}$/),
  secondary_color: z.string().regex(/^#[0-9a-fA-F]{6}$/),
  accent_color: z.string().regex(/^#[0-9a-fA-F]{6}$/),
  font_family: z.string().max(60),
});
```

